text.tspan: Per capita GHG emissions vs. Per capita CO₂ emissions (excl. land use),
Total greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions are measured in carbon dioxide-equivalents (CO₂e), based on 100-year global
warming potential factors for non-CO₂ gases. Emissions from land use change and forestry are not included in either metric.
Per capita GHG emissions (excl. land use)
Source: CAIT Climate Data Explorer, Our World in Data based on the Global Carbon Project
